## Ablation Study

### Experimental Protocol

**Phase 1: Quick Validation (2 days)**
```bash
# 1. Train uniform mix for 5K steps
python train_gear5.py \
  --config configs/gear5/ablation_uniform_mix.yaml \
  training.iterations=5000 \
  model.use_uniform_mix=true \
  results_dir=ablation/uniform_mix

# 2. Train concat for 5K steps (from same init)
python train_gear5.py \
  --config configs/gear5/ablation_concat.yaml \
  training.iterations=5000 \
  model.use_uniform_mix=false \
  results_dir=ablation/concat

# 3. Compare validation metrics
python compare_ablation.py \
  --variant1 ablation/uniform_mix \
  --variant2 ablation/concat
```

**Phase 2: Full Training (1 week each)**
- Train both to convergence (~50K steps)
- Monitor training curves
- Compare best checkpoints

**Phase 3: Comprehensive Testing**
```bash
# Test on all datasets
for method in uniform_mix concat; do
  python test_gear5.py \
    --checkpoint ablation/${method}/best.pth \
    --dataset waymo,sintel,kitti \
    --results-dir ablation/${method}/test_results
done
```

### Metrics to Compare

| Category | Metrics |
|----------|---------|
| **Accuracy** | MAE, RMSE, AbsRel, δ1/δ2/δ3, Boundary F1 |
| **Temporal** | TAE (frame-to-frame consistency) |
| **Speed** | FPS, inference time |
| **Training** | Loss curves, convergence speed, stability |
| **Object-wise** | Per-class metrics (vehicle, pedestrian, etc.) |

